RETRY GUIDANCE (failCount: 2): Previous failures likely due to overly complex error mapping or TypeScript issues. Keep it simple.

IMPLEMENTATION APPROACH — minimal surface area:

(1) Create src/cli/errors.ts with a single exported function:
```typescript
import { formatError } from './ui.js';

export function handleCliError(err: unknown): void {
  const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
  const stack = err instanceof Error ? err.stack ?? '' : '';

  if (message.includes('ENOENT') && (message.includes('docker') || stack.includes('docker'))) {
    formatError('DOCKER_NOT_FOUND', 'Docker is not installed or not in PATH', 'Install Docker Desktop from docker.com and ensure it is running');
  } else if (message.includes('ECONNREFUSED') || message.includes('Cannot connect to Docker')) {
    formatError('DOCKER_NOT_RUNNING', 'Docker daemon is not running', 'Start Docker Desktop or run: sudo systemctl start docker');
  } else if (message.includes('openclaw.json') && (message.includes('ENOENT') || message.includes('not found'))) {
    formatError('NO_CONFIG', 'No agent config found', 'Run: clawhq init to set up your agent');
  } else if (message.includes('EADDRINUSE')) {
    formatError('PORT_IN_USE', 'Port is already in use', 'Check what is using the port: lsof -i :<port>');
  } else if (message.includes('Dockerfile') && (message.includes('not found') || message.includes('ENOENT'))) {
    formatError('NO_DOCKERFILE', 'Dockerfile not found — run clawhq build first', 'Run: clawhq build to generate the Dockerfile');
  } else if (message.includes('EACCES') && message.includes('.env')) {
    formatError('PERMISSION_DENIED', 'Permission denied reading .env file', 'Fix permissions: chmod 600 .env');
  } else {
    formatError('UNKNOWN_ERROR', message || 'An unexpected error occurred', 'Run with DEBUG=1 for full details');
  }
}
```

(2) In src/cli/index.ts, wrap the program.parseAsync() call:
```typescript
import { handleCliError } from './errors.js';

program.parseAsync(process.argv).catch((err) => {
  handleCliError(err);
  process.exit(1);
});
```

VALIDATOR ACs (all locally checkable):
- src/cli/errors.ts exists and exports handleCliError(err: unknown): void
- handleCliError covers exactly 6 error cases: DOCKER_NOT_FOUND, DOCKER_NOT_RUNNING, NO_CONFIG, PORT_IN_USE, NO_DOCKERFILE, PERMISSION_DENIED
- Unknown errors show UNKNOWN_ERROR not a stack trace
- program.parseAsync() in index.ts is wrapped in .catch(handleCliError)
- tsc --noEmit passes clean
- No regression: existing commands still work (test with clawhq --version)
